headline: European intelligence services adapt to the upheavals of the Trump era
description: Shaken by Donald Trump's unpredictable behavior, European intelligence services, long reliant on the United States, are tightening their cooperation.

French far right's EU embezzlement was 'directed by' Le Pen, prosecutors argue
description: Prosecutors at Marine Le Pen's appeal trial requested a four-year prison sentence and a five-year ban on being elected to office for the far-right leader, describing her as 'the instigator, following her father, of a system that allowed her to embezzle €1.4 million.'

headline: How France's lottery operator fuels the toxic online casino ecosystem in the Comoros
description: The Comorian island of Anjouan has gained a reputation as a haven for online casinos with illegal and harmful practices. Yet a subsidiary of Française des Jeux recently obtained a questionable license there to provide its iGaming services.

headline: Italy says it stopped Russian-linked cyberattacks targeting 2026 Winter Olympics sites
description: Just hours before the first sporting events, Foreign Minister Antonio Tajani said Italy had foiled a series of Russian cyberattacks targeting foreign ministry offices and Winter Olympics sites, including hotels in Cortina.

headline: Ukraine's 'grandfathers' go to war
description: The Ukrainian army has an average age of 45, significantly older than European standards. The draft has targeted men between the ages of 25 and 60, which contrasts with recruitment practices typically seen in Western countries.

description: 'I wouldn't be where I am today if...' In this series, Le Monde interviews a personality about a decisive moment in their life. The figure skater and former Olympic champion looks back on a childhood filled with constraints in order to succeed in a demanding and conservative environment.

headline: Mark Carney, a prime minister seeking to free Canada from US dominance
description: As the international order weakens, the Canadian leader has moved on from the Trudeau era, when his predecessor was seen as naive on the world stage, and to assert himself against hegemonic powers – starting with his American neighbor.

headline: Blocking the Russian army: Ukraine's impossible mission
description: With limited technical and human resources, soldiers and engineers in these units, increasingly exposed to drone fire, are trying to contain the Russian army, which continues to make slow but steady advances.
